Sports Analysis C++ README
Nicholas Houghton

This program reads a file of player statistics, applies updates from a second file, and outputs the updated data. Each playerâ€™s stats are adjusted based on the input.
The program has configurable stat and player counts through command-line arguments.

To compile:
make

To run:
./teamData oldData.txt newData.txt outName.txt numStats numPlayers

Example:
./teamData simple_data.txt simple_update.txt simple_out.txt 4 2
Example Output:
ID	FirstName	LastName	points	catches	throws	games
0	  PlayerA		PlayerA		2		    6		    6		    2
1	  PlayerB		PlayerB		8		    17		  5		    4


